    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 811.001/338</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Armenian National Delegation</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-04">July 4,
                            1919</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: I have the honour to enclose herewith a
                    message to President Wilson signed by Mr. Veniselos, Mr. Pashitch, Dr. Benes,
                        <pb facs="0646" n="608" xml:id="pg_608"/> Boghos Nubar Pasha and Mr.
                        Sokolow,<note n="65" xml:id="d278fn65">Representatives of the Greek,
                        Jugoslav, Czechoslovak, Armenian, and Zionist delegations,
                        respectively.</note> which I shall feel greatly obliged if you will kindly
                    transmit to His Excellency by wireless at your earliest convenience.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James A. Malcolm</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>For the Armenian National Delegation</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
